      "schema:description": "MEOP (Marine Mammals Exploring the Oceans Pole to Pole) is a consortium of international researchers dedicated to sharing animal-derived data and knowledge about the polar oceans. Collectively, MEOP demonstrates the power and cost-effectiveness of using marine mammals as data-collection platforms that can dramatically improve the ocean-observing system for biological and physical oceanographers.\r\nFor the Australian group, deployments were done at Macquarie Island, Campbell Island, Kerguelen Island,  Davis station, Casey station and McMurdo Station Ross Sea.\r\nSupporting institution: the Integrated Marine Observing System (IMOS)",
